Vice President Biden will be visiting Ukraine to show the United States' support for Ukraine's democracy, unity, sovereignty, and territorial integrity. He will meet with various Ukrainian officials, including acting President Turchynov and Prime Minister Yatsenyuk, to discuss national unity and constitutional reform. Biden will also meet with members of civil society to address issues such as democracy, anti-corruption, and youth issues. He will discuss economic stabilization, energy assistance, and forms of U.S. assistance. The Vice President will also address the recent violence in Ukraine and call for Russia to de-escalate the situation. The goal of the trip is to support Ukraine's efforts to tackle urgent challenges and promote national unity.